condition.narrative: Borrower shall ensure that the Project is carried out in accordance with the POM and Service Guidelines on Community Participation
Borrower shall implement the Project in accordance with ESMF and RPF
Borrower shall maintain LGA Finance Committees which shall be responsible for overseeing implementation of the Project at thelocalgovernment level
Borrower shall maintain the NSC under terms of reference and with membership composition satisfactory to the Association
Borrower shall maintain the TASAF MU for duration of the Project with staffing and resources satisfactory to the Associaiton
Borrower shall maintain throughout Project Implementation a SET to provide the NSC with advice regarding the compliance ofproposedsubprojects with sector norms and standards
Borrower shall prepare and furnish to Association a report integrating results of monitoring and evaluation activities, progressachieved, recommended measures and achievement of objectives (MTR)
Borrower shall prepare and submit to Association annual progress reports on or about September 30th of each year of Projectimplementation
Borrower shall update the Procurement Plan in accordance with guidelines acceptable to the Association, and furnish such updatenotlater than 12 months after the date of the preceding Plan
CMC shall prepare quarterly progress reports including financial reports for submission to the Village Council and consolidatedsubmission by LGAs to TASAF MU and SET
Each village shall establish a Village Fund in accordance with provisions of LGA Act, into which TASAF MU shall disburse fundsfromNVF
Regional Commissioners shall maintain throughout Project implementation a Regional Consultative Committee to monitor progress madeby LGAs in developing resource accountability measures
TASAF MU shall enter into a Memorandum of Understanding with each LGA participating in the Project, setting forth respectiveresponsiblities at each stage of subproject cycle
The respective LGA and VC shall enter into a subproject financing agreement with each CMC under terms/conditions satisfactory tothe Association
